Functions.Name: Dir
Functions.Comment:
Dir returns a http.Filesystem for the embedded assets on a given prefix dir.
If useLocal is true, the filesystem's contents are instead used.

Functions.Name: FS
Functions.Comment:
FS returns a http.Filesystem for the embedded assets. If useLocal is true,
the filesystem's contents are instead used.

Functions.Name: FSByte
Functions.Comment:
FSByte returns the named file from the embedded assets. If useLocal is
true, the filesystem's contents are instead used.

Functions.Name: FSMustByte
Functions.Comment: FSMustByte is the same as FSByte, but panics if name is not present.

Functions.Name: FSMustString
Functions.Comment: FSMustString is the string version of FSMustByte.

Functions.Name: FSString
Functions.Comment: FSString is the string version of FSByte.

Functions.Name: CurrentTime
Functions.Comment: Returns the current time every time the field is persisted.

Functions.Name: CurrentTimeIfUnset
Functions.Comment: Returns the current time when the field is persisted if the current value is empty.

Functions.Name: DeriveFromFields
Functions.Comment: Extracts values from the given Record and generates a deterministic output based on those values.

Functions.Name: GenerateEncodedUUID
Functions.Comment: Same as GenerateUUID, but allows for a custom representation of the underlying bytes.

Functions.Name: GenerateUUID
Functions.Comment: Generates a V4 UUID value if the existing value is empty.

Functions.Name: IfUnset
Functions.Comment: Only evaluates the given formatter if the current value of the field is empty.

Functions.Name: NowPlusDuration
Functions.Comment: Returns the current time with an added offset when the field is persisted.

Functions.Name: ShouldCreateCollection
Functions.Comment:
Takes a collection definition and any errors encountered while retrieving it, and determines
whether a CreateCollection() call should be made.

Functions.Name: ValidateIsURL
Functions.Comment: Validate that the value is a URL with a non-empty scheme and host component.

Functions.Name: ValidateNonZero
Functions.Comment: Validate that the given value is not a zero value (false, 0, 0.0, "", null).

Functions.Name: ValidateNotEmpty
Functions.Comment:
Validate that the given value is not a zero value, and if it's a string, that the string
does not contain only whitespace.

Functions.Name: ValidatePositiveInteger
Functions.Comment: Validate that the given value is an integer > 0.

Functions.Name: ValidatePositiveOrZeroInteger
Functions.Comment: Validate that the given value is an integer >= 0.

Methods.Name: AddFields
Methods.Comment: Append a field definition to this collection.

Methods.Name: ApplyDefinition
Methods.Comment:
Copies certain collection and field properties from the definition object into this collection
instance.  This is useful for collections that are created by parsing the schema as it exists on
the remote datastore, which will have some but not all of the information we need to work with the
data.  Definition collections are the authoritative source for things like what the default value
should be, and which validators and formatters apply to a given field.

This function converts this instance into a Collection definition by copying the relevant values
from given definition.

Methods.Name: Check
Methods.Comment: Verifies that the schema passes some basic sanity checks.

Methods.Name: ConvertValue
Methods.Comment: Convert a given value according to the data type of a specific named field.

Methods.Name: Diff
Methods.Comment: Determine the differences (if any) between this Collection definition and another.

Methods.Name: FillDefaults
Methods.Comment: Populate a given Record with the default values (if any) of all fields in the Collection.

Methods.Name: GetAggregatorName
Methods.Comment: Get the canonical name of the dataset in an external aggregator service.

Methods.Name: GetAllConstraints
Methods.Comment:
Retrieve the set of all Constraints on this collection, both explicitly provided
via the Constraints field, as well as constraints specified using the "BelongsTo"
shorthand on Fields.

Methods.Name: GetField
Methods.Comment:
Retrieve a single field by name.  The second return value will be false if the field does not
exist.

Methods.Name: GetFieldByIndex
Methods.Comment:
Retrieve a single field by its index value. The second return value will be false if a field
at that index does not exist.

Methods.Name: GetFirstNonIdentityKeyField
Methods.Comment: Retrieve the first non-indentity key field, sometimes referred to as the "range", "sort", or "cluster" key.

Methods.Name: GetIdentityFieldName
Methods.Comment: Get the canonical name of the primary identity field.

Methods.Name: GetIndexName
Methods.Comment: Get the canonical name of the external index name.

Methods.Name: GetRelatedCollection
Methods.Comment: Retrieves a Collection by name from the backend this Collection is registered to.

Methods.Name: IsExpired
Methods.Comment: Expired records are those whose TTL duration is non-zero and negative.

Methods.Name: IsIdentityField
Methods.Comment: TODO: what is this?

Methods.Name: IsKeyField
Methods.Comment: Return whether a given field name is a key on this Collection.

Methods.Name: KeyCount
Methods.Comment: Return the number of keys on that uniquely identify a single record in this Collection.

Methods.Name: KeyFieldNames
Methods.Comment: Same as KeyFields, but returns only the field names

Methods.Name: KeyFields
Methods.Comment:
Retrieve all of the fields that comprise the primary key for this Collection.  This will always include the identity
field at a minimum.

Methods.Name: MakeRecord
Methods.Comment: Deprecated: use StructToRecord instead

Methods.Name: MapFromRecord
Methods.Comment: Convert the given record into a map.

Methods.Name: NewCollection
Methods.Comment: Create a new colllection definition with no fields.

Methods.Name: SetBackend
Methods.Comment:
Set the backend for this collection.  The Backend interface in this package is a limited subset
of the backends.Backend interface that avoids a circular dependency between the two packages.
The intent is to allow Collections to retrieve details about other collections registered on the
same backend.

Methods.Name: SetIdentity
Methods.Comment: Configure the identity field of a collection in a single function call.
Methods.Signature: SetIdentity(name string, idtype Type, formatter FieldFormatterFunc, validator FieldValidatorFunc) *Collection

Methods.Name: SetRecordType
Methods.Comment: Deprecated: this functionality has been removed.

Methods.Name: StructToRecord
Methods.Comment: Generates a Record suitable for persistence in a backend from the given struct.

Methods.Name: TTL
Methods.Comment:
Return the duration until the TimeToLiveField in given record expires within the current collection.
Collections with an empty TimeToLiveField, or records with a missing or zero-valued TimeToLiveField
will return 0.  If the record has already expired, the returned duration will be a negative number.

Methods.Name: ValidateRecord
Methods.Comment: Validate the given record against all Field and Collection validators.

Methods.Name: ValueForField
Methods.Comment:
Convert a given value into one that that can go into the backend database (for create/update operations), or that
should be returned to the user (for retrieval operations) in accordance with the named field's data type and
formatters.  Invalid values (determined by Validators and the Required option in the Field) will return an error.
Methods.Signature: ValueForField(name string, value interface{}, op FieldOperation) (interface{}, error)

Fields.Name: Name
Fields.Comment: The name of the collection

Fields.Name: IndexName
Fields.Comment: The name of the associated external inverted index used to query this collection.

Fields.Name: IndexCompoundFields
Fields.Comment:
Lists the field names that make up a composite key on this Collection that should be joined
together when determining index record IDs.  Often it is the case that external indices do
not support composite keys the way databases do, so this allows Collections with composite
keys to be indexed in those systems by joining several values together to form a unique key.

Fields.Name: IndexCompoundFieldJoiner
Fields.Comment: The string used to join and split ID values that go into / come out of external indices.

Fields.Name: SkipIndexPersistence
Fields.Comment: Disable automatically dual-writing modified records into the external index.

Fields.Name: Fields
Fields.Comment:
The fields that belong to this collection (all except the primary key/identity field/first
field in a composite key)

Fields.Name: IdentityField
Fields.Comment: The name of the identity field for this Collection.  Defaults to "id".

Fields.Name: IdentityFieldType
Fields.Comment: The datatype of the identity field.  Defaults to integer.

Fields.Name: IdentityFieldIndex
Fields.Comment: Used to store the location of the identity field in the source database.

Fields.Name: EmbeddedCollections
Fields.Comment:
Specifies how fields in this Collection relate to records from other collections.  This is
a partial implementation of a relational model, specifically capturing one-to-one or
one-to-many relationships.  The definitions here will retrieve the associated records from
another, and those values will replace the value that is actually in this Collection's field.

Fields.Name: Constraints
Fields.Comment:
Allows for constraints to be applied to a collection.  In addition to informing Pivot about the
relationships between collections, this data is also used to enforce referential integrity for
backends that support such guarantees (e.g.: ACID-compliant RDBMS').

Fields.Name: ExportedFields
Fields.Comment:
Specifies which fields can be seen when records are from relationships defined on other
Collections.  This can be used to restrict the exposure) of sensitive data in this Collection
be being an embedded field in another Collection.

Fields.Name: AllowMissingEmbeddedRecords
Fields.Comment: Specify whether missing related fields generate an error when retrieving a record.

Fields.Name: TotalRecords
Fields.Comment: A read-only count of the number of records in this Collection

Fields.Name: TotalRecordsExact
Fields.Comment:
Whether the value of TotalRecords represents an exact (authoritative) count or an
approximate count.

Fields.Name: TimeToLiveField
Fields.Comment:
The name of a field containing an absolute datetime after which expired records should be
deleted from this Collection.

Fields.Name: IdentityFieldFormatter
Fields.Comment:
A function that modifies the identity key value before any operation.  Operates the same as
a Field Formatter function.

Fields.Name: AutoIdentity
Fields.Comment: Specifies that IDs should be automatically generated using a formatter function

Fields.Name: IdentityFieldValidator
Fields.Comment:
A function that validates the value of an identity key before create and update operations.
Operates the same as a Field Validator function.

Fields.Name: SourceURI
Fields.Comment: Allow backends to store internal information about the backing datasource for this collection.

Fields.Name: PreSaveValidator
Fields.Comment:
If specified, this function receives a copy of the populated record before create and update
operations, allowing for a last-chance validation of the record as a whole.  Use a pre-save
validator when validation requires checking multiple fields at once.

Fields.Name: View
Fields.Comment: Specifies that this collection is a read-only view on data that is queried by the underlying database engine.

Fields.Name: ViewKeywords
Fields.Comment: Specify additional keywords in the view creation to modify how it is created.

Fields.Name: ViewQuery
Fields.Comment: A query object that is passed to the underlying database engine.

Fields.Name: AlwaysCreate
Fields.Comment: Specifies that creating this collection on the backend should always be attempted.

Methods.Name: Backend
Methods.Comment: Returns the backend component of the string.

Methods.Name: Credentials
Methods.Comment:
Return the credentials (if any) associated with this string, and whether they
were present or not.

Methods.Name: Dataset
Methods.Comment: Returns the dataset component of the string.

Methods.Name: Host
Methods.Comment: Returns the host component of the string.

Methods.Name: LoadCredentialsFromNetrc
Methods.Comment:
Reads a .netrc-style file and loads the appropriate credentials.  The host component of
this connection string is matched with the netrc "machine" field.

Methods.Name: Protocol
Methods.Comment: Returns the protocol component of the string.

Methods.Name: Scheme
Methods.Comment: Returns the backend and protocol components of the string.

Methods.Name: SetCredentials
Methods.Comment: Explicitly set username and password on this connection string

Methods.Name: MakeConnectionString
Methods.Signature: MakeConnectionString(scheme string, host string, dataset string, options map[string]interface{}) (ConnectionString, error)

Fields.Name: On
Fields.Comment: Represents the name (or array of names) of the local field the constraint is being applied to.

Fields.Name: Collection
Fields.Comment: The remote collection the constraint applies to.

Fields.Name: Field
Fields.Comment: The remote field (or fields) in the remote collection the constraint applies to.

Fields.Name: Options
Fields.Comment: Provides backend-specific additional options for the constraint.

Fields.Name: Into
Fields.Comment: Specifies the local field that related records will be put into.  Defaults to the field specified in On.

Fields.Name: NoEmbed
Fields.Comment: Whether to omit this constraint when determining embedded collections.

Methods.Name: BelongsToConstraint
Methods.Comment: Parses the value of BelongsTo into a valid Constraint

Fields.Name: Name
Fields.Comment: The name of the field

Fields.Name: Description
Fields.Comment: A description of the field used in help text

Fields.Name: Type
Fields.Comment: The data type of the field

Fields.Name: KeyType
Fields.Comment: For complex field types (tuples, objects); the data type of the key portion

Fields.Name: Subtype
Fields.Comment: For complex field types (arrays, sets, lists); the data type of the contained values

Fields.Name: Length
Fields.Comment: The length constraint for values in the field (where supported)

Fields.Name: Precision
Fields.Comment: The precision of stored values in the field (where supported)

Fields.Name: Identity
Fields.Comment:
Whether the field is an identity field (don't use this, configure the identity on the
Collection instead)

Fields.Name: Key
Fields.Comment: Whether the field is a key field in a composite key Collection

Fields.Name: Required
Fields.Comment: Whether the field can store a null/empty value

Fields.Name: Unique
Fields.Comment: Enforces that the field value must be unique across the entire Collection (where supported)

Fields.Name: UniqueGroup
Fields.Comment:
The name of a group of unique fields that, taken together, must be unique across the entire
Collection (where supported)

Fields.Name: DefaultValue
Fields.Comment:
The default value of the field is one is not explicitly specified.  Can be any type or a
function that takes zero arguments and returns a single value.

Fields.Name: NativeType
Fields.Comment: Represents the native datatype of the underlying Backend object (read only)

Fields.Name: NotUserEditable
Fields.Comment:
Specify that the field should not be modified.  This is not enforced in Pivot, but rather
serves as a note to applications implementing interactions with the Pivot API.

Fields.Name: ValidateOnPopulate
Fields.Comment:
Whether this field's validator(s) should be used to validate data being retrieved from the
backend.  Invalid data (possibly created outside of Pivot) will cause Retrieve() calls to
return a validation error.

Fields.Name: Validator
Fields.Comment:
A function that is used to validate the field's value before performing any create, update,
and (optionally) retrieval operations.

Fields.Name: Formatter
Fields.Comment:
A function that can modify values before any create or update operations.  Formatters run
before Validators, giving users the opportunity to ensure a valid value is in the data
structure before validation runs.

Fields.Name: ValidatorConfig
Fields.Comment:
A declarative form of the Validator configuration that uses pre-defined validators. Primarily
used when storing schema declarations in external JSON files.

Fields.Name: FormatterConfig
Fields.Comment:
A declarative form of the Formatter configuration that uses pre-defined validators. Primarily
used when storing schema declarations in external JSON files.

Fields.Name: Index
Fields.Comment: Used to store the order this field appears in the source database.

Fields.Name: BelongsTo
Fields.Comment:
Specify a relationship between this field and another collection.

If given a string, it will be interpreted as a collection name and a
constaint against that collection's identity field will be created.

If given a *Collection, the same behavior as above will occur, but using
the Collection.Name from the given struct.

If given a Constraint, the constraint will be added to this field's
parent collection with the "On" field set to this field's name.

Fields.Name: ReadOnly
Fields.Comment: Specifies that the field may not be updated, only read.  Attempts to update the field will be silently discarded.

Methods.Name: ValidatorFromMap
Methods.Comment: Retrieve a validator by name.  Used by the ValidatorConfig configuration on Field.

Methods.Name: GetValidator
Methods.Comment: Retrieve a validator by name.  Used by the ValidatorConfig configuration on Field.

Methods.Name: ValidateMatchAll
Methods.Comment: Validate that the given value matches all of the given regular expressions.

Methods.Name: ValidateMatchAny
Methods.Comment: Validate that the given value matches at least one of the given regular expressions.

Methods.Name: ValidateAll
Methods.Comment: Validate that all of the given validator functions pass.

Methods.Name: ValidateIsOneOf
Methods.Comment: Validate that the given value is among the given choices.

Methods.Name: Populate
Methods.Comment: Populates a given struct with with the values in this record.

Methods.Name: PopulateFromRecords
Methods.Comment:
Takes a slice of structs or maps and fills it with instances populated by the records in this RecordSet
in accordance with the types specified in the given collection definition, as well as which
fields are available in the given struct.

Functions.Name: Render
Functions.Signature: Render(generator IGenerator, collectionName string, filter *Filter) ([]byte, error)

Methods.Name: ParseSpec
Methods.Comment: Filter syntax definition

Methods.Name: Finalize
Methods.Comment: Takes all the information collected so far and generates a SQL statement from it

Methods.Name: ToNativeType
Methods.Signature: ToNativeType(in dal.Type, subtypes []dal.Type, length int) (string, error)

Methods.Name: ToNativeValue
Methods.Signature: ToNativeValue(t dal.Type, subtypes []dal.Type, in interface{}) string

Methods.Name: Create
Methods.Comment: Creates and saves a new instance of the model from the given struct or dal.Record.

Methods.Name: CreateOrUpdate
Methods.Comment: Creates or updates an instance of the model depending on whether it exists or not.

Methods.Name: Delete
Methods.Comment: Delete instances of the model identified by the given IDs

Methods.Name: DeleteQuery
Methods.Comment: Delete all records matching the given query.

Methods.Name: Exists
Methods.Comment: Tests whether a record exists for the given ID.

Methods.Name: Find
Methods.Comment:
Perform a query for instances of the model that match the given filter.Filter.
Results will be returned in the slice or array pointed to by the into parameter, or
if into points to a dal.RecordSet, the RecordSet resulting from the query will be returned
as-is.

Methods.Name: FindFunc
Methods.Comment:
Perform a query for instances of the model that match the given filter.Filter.
The given callback function will be called once per result.
Methods.Signature: FindFunc(flt interface{}, destZeroValue interface{}, resultFn ResultFunc) error

Methods.Name: Get
Methods.Comment:
Retrieves an instance of the model identified by the given ID and populates the value pointed to
by the into parameter.  Structs and dal.Record instances can be populated.

Methods.Name: Update
Methods.Comment: Updates and saves an existing instance of the model from the given struct or dal.Record.
